Jobilis v1.0 1stPass UI [Feature]: App crash in edit with no internet
[Summary]
 When the manage job post was used with no internet connectivity, the app crashes.

[Precondition]
 Software version: Jobilis v1.o
 Software configuration: Default Settings, light theme
 Hardware specifications: Screen Size
 Network configuration: Offline scenario tested

[Steps to reproduce]
 1. Ensure that the device is not connected to the internet.
 2. Launch the Jobilis app
 3. Navigate to profile in the bottom navigation bar
 4. Click the `Manage Jobs` tab in the  `Job Post Management`
 5. Click edit on any of the existing job posts
 6. Observe the behavior of the app.
 

[Actual results]
 The app crashes as soon as edit button was clicked.

[Expected results]
 The app should alert the user about no connectivity to internet and not to suddenly crash.
[Additional information]
 A screenshot of the outcome has been attached for reference. No runtime logs were captured, as the QA team was provided only with an APK build. Additionally, the app is developed using Visual Studio with C# and MAUI, which requires specific configuration settings to enable logging or debug access.

[Is this Breakage?]
 No, new implementation

[Previous code tested]
 MC.010.003
 
[Severity: How does this problem impact the customer/user?]
 6. Crash or hang cleared by restart
 
[Likelihood: How often will a customer/user use this feature/function?]
 8. Moderate

[Repeatability: Is this problem easily reproducible?]
 10. 100% Reproducible

[Impacted Test Cases]
   MANP-0001

[Impact Sizing (in days)]
 Less than a day